@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor "Alice" as Alice
participant "Coordinator" as Coord
participant "<&hard-drive> Disk" as Disk
participant "Recovery" as Recovery

== Run 1 ==
Alice -> Coord : write "After Dawn"
Coord -> Disk : flush write
Disk -> Disk : persist
Coord -[#red]x Coord : crash
Recovery -> Disk : recover state
Disk -[#green]> Recovery : "After Dawn" present

== Run 2 ==
Alice -> Coord : write "After Dawn"
Coord -> Disk : flush write
Coord -[#red]x Coord : crash
Disk -> Disk : flush not completed
Recovery -> Disk : recover state
Disk -[#red]> Recovery : "After Dawn" missing

note over Alice, Recovery
The same crash can produce different recovered state
depending on whether the write reached durable storage.
end note
@enduml
